The Vice President, Mike Pence, visited the First Baptist Church in Sutherland Springs, Texas, following the recent mass shooting. He expressed condolences and support for the community, stating that the American people are with them. Pence also mentioned that the government is providing federal resources to the state and local authorities, and that investigations are being conducted into how the shooter was able to obtain a firearm despite his history of mental illness. He praised the heroes who responded to the attack, including the first responders and the two Texas citizens who confronted the assailant. Pence emphasized the strength of faith in this community and urged Americans to keep them in their prayers. He assured the community that the federal government is committed to supporting the investigation and helping the affected families.